definitions.definition: To end ; to come to an end .
examples: The story concluded with a moral.

definitions.definition: To bring to an end; to close; to finish.
To bring about as a result; to effect; to make.
To come to a conclusion , to a final decision .
examples: From the evidence, I conclude that this man was murdered.

definitions.definition: To make a final determination or judgment concerning; to judge; to decide.
To shut off; to restrain; to limit; to estop ; to bar .
examples: The defendant is concluded by his own plea.
A judgment concludes the introduction of further evidence.

definitions.definition: To include; to comprehend; to shut up together; to embrace; to confine .
to deduce , to infer ( develop a causal relation )

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To end ; to come to an end .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To bring to an end; to close; to finish.
( transitive ) To bring about as a result; to effect; to make.
( transitive ) To come to a conclusion , to a final decision .
( obsolete ) To make a final determination or judgment concerning; to judge; to decide.
( often passive voice ) To shut off; to restrain; to limit; to estop ; to bar .
( obsolete ) To shut up; to enclose .
( obsolete ) To include; to comprehend; to shut up together; to embrace; to confine .
( logic ) to deduce , to infer ( develop a causal relation )
